<h2><a name='naming'>Naming Conventions:</a></h2>
<set name='name'><em>AppName</em></set>


<dl>
  <dt> <a href='/~&AGENT:name;/'>/~&name;/</a>
  </dt>
  <dd> An alias for the &name; agent's home directory.
  </dd>
  <dt> <a href='/~&AGENT:name;/-'>/~&name;/-</a>
  </dt>
  <dd> A generic listing of an application's home directory.  This will work
       with <em>any</em> directory, not just agent homes, although it can be
       hidden by the site designer.  For example, <a
       href="/-"><code>/-</code></a> gives a generic listing of the PIA's home
       directory. 
  </dd>
  <dt> <a href='/~&AGENT:name;/DATA/'>/~&name;/DATA/</a>
  </dt>
  <dd> Usually the application's data directory, if it has one.  This is just
       a convention that may not be universal.
  </dd>
  <dt> <a href='/~&AGENT:name;/DATA/-'>/~&name;/.</a>
  </dt>
  <dd> A generic listing of the data directory.
       </dd>
</dl>


